HEADWORD: Mutule
<hw>Mu"tule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>mutulus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A projecting block
worked under the corona of the Doric corice, in the same situation as
the modillion of the Corinthian and Composite orders. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Gutta</er>.</def> <rj><au>Oxf.
Gloss.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

